HEADWORD: Euplexoptera
<hw>Eu`plex*op"te*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ to plait + <?/ a wing.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>An order of insects, including the earwig.
The anterior wings are short, in the form of elytra, while the posterior
wings fold up beneath them. See <er>Earwig</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

